e;text-align:left;\"|'''Total''' || '''24,726,344''' || '''11,466,329''' || '''7,893,055''' || '''627,527''' || '''33,244''' || '''33,645''' || '''903,545''' || '''88,499'''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Ethnic groups===\nNortheast India has over 220 ethnic groups and an equal number of dialects in which [[Bodo people|Bodo]] form the largest indigenous ethnic group.<ref name=\"Tribal groups in Assam and Northeast India\">{{Cite web |url=http://factsanddetails.com/india/Minorities_Castes_and_Regions_in_India/sub7_4f/entry-4210.html |title=Tribal groups in Assam and Northeast India}}</ref> The hills states in the region like [[Arunachal Pradesh]], [[Meghalaya]], [[Mizoram]], and [[Nagaland]] are predominantly inhabited by tribal people with a degree of diversity even within the tribal groups. The region's population results from ancient and continuous flows of migrations from Tibet, Indo-Gangetic India, the Himalayas, present Bangladesh, and Myanmar.<ref>van Driem, G. (2012)</ref>\n\n====Major communities====\n{{colbegin|colwidth=10em}}\n{{plainlist|\n* [[Adivasi]]\n* [[Ahom people|Ahom]]\n* [[Angami Naga|Angami]]\n* [[Ao Naga|Ao]]\n* [[An\u0101l Naga]]\n* [[Apatani people|Apatani]]\n* [[Assamese people|Assamese]]\n* [[Bahun]]\n* [[Bengali people|Bengali]] \n* [[Bhutia]]\n* [[Bisnupriya Manipuri people|Bishnupriya]]\n* [[Biate people|Biate]]\n* [[Bodo people|Bodo]]\n* [[Bru people|Bru]]\n* [[Chakhesang]]\n* [[Chakma people|Chakma]]\n* [[Chhetri]]\n* [[Chutiya]]\n* [[Chorei language|Chorei]]\n* [[Deori people|Deori]]\n* [[Dimasa people|Dimasa]]\n* [[Garo people|Garo]]\n* [[Gurung people|Gurung]]\n* [[Hajong people|Hajong]]\n* [[Hmar people|Hmar]]\n* [[Jamatia]]\n* [[Karbi people|Karbi]]\n* [[Kami]]\n* [[Khasi people|Khasi]]\n* [[Khampti]]\n* [[Koch Rajbongshi people|Koch]]\n* [[Kom people (India)|Kom]]\n* [[Konyak people|Konyak]]\n* [[Kuki people|Kuki]]\n* [[Lepcha people|Lepcha]]\n* [[Limbu]]\n* [[Lotha Naga|Lotha]]\n* [[Magar (Maharashtra)|Magar]]\n* [[Mao Naga|Mao]]\n* [[Maram Naga|Maram]]\n* [[Meitei people|Meitei]]\n* [[Mishing People|Mishing]]\n* [[Mizo people|Mizo]]\n* [[Mara people|Mara]]\n* [[Monsang Naga|Monsang]]\n* [[Mishmi people|Mishmi]]\n* [[Naga people|Naga]]\n* [[People of Nepal|Nepali]]\n* [[Noatia]] \n* [[Paite people|Paite]]\n* [[Pnar people|Pnar]]\n* [[Poumai Naga|Poumai]]\n* [[Purvottar maithili]]\n* [[Rai (ethnic group)|Rai]]\n* [[Rabha]]\n* [[Ranglong language|Ranglong]] (''Langrong'')\n* [[Reang]]\n* [[Rongmei Naga|Rongmei]]\n* [[Sangtam Naga|Sangtam]]\n* [[Sumi Naga|Sumi]]\n* [[Singpho people|Singpho]]\n*[[Sonowal Kachari]]\n* [[Sylheti language|Sylheti]]\n* [[Tamang people|Tamang]]\n* [[Tangkhul Naga|Tangkhul]]\n* [[Tiwa (Lalung)|Tiwa]]\n* [[Thengal Kachari]]\n* [[Tripuri people|Tripuri]]\n* [[Yimchunger]]\n* [[Zomi people]] (Paite, Vaiphei, Zou, Teddim, Simte, Gangte)\n}}\n{{colend}}\n<br />\n<gallery>\nFile:British India map of Northeast India and Myanmar, Bengal Assam Meghalaya Arunachal Pradesh Nagaland Manipur Mizoram Tripura regions 1891.jpg|<center>British India map of Northeast India by ethnicity, 1891</center>\nFile:\u0422\u0430\u043d\u0446\u043e\u0440 \u043f\u043b\u0435\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0433\u0430.JPG|<center>A [[Naga people|Naga]] warrior in 1960</center>\nFile:Bishnupriya Manipuri Bride.jpg|<center>[[Bisnupriya Manipuri Society|Bishnupuriya]] bride</center>\nFile:SHAD SUK MYNSIEM.jpg|<center>Shad suk Mynsiem, a [[Khasi people|Khasi]] festival</center>\nFile:Traditional Hajong Clothing, Pathin and Argon.jpg|<center>Traditional [[Hajong people|Hajong]] Clothing</center>\nFile:Aka Tribe.jpg|<center>Aka tribe, [[Arunachal Pradesh]]</center>\nFile:Mizo school girls.jpg|<center>[[Mizo people|Mizo]] school girls</center>\nFile:Fruit sellers in Senapati, Manipur, India..JPG|<center>Women selling fruits in [[Senapati district|Senapati]], [[Manipur]]</center>\nFile:Sister of the King of Sikkim in traditional royal dress, 30214u.tif|<center>Princess of [[Sikkim]] in traditional royal dress</center